of relatives of passengers squatted on a sidewalk or huddled in taxis awaiting word about their kin hassan al-aghouri egypt's chief of port security said the egyptian-registered ferry inexplicably left standard navigational channels and investigators were seeking to question surviving crew about the course change the investigation also will try to determine whether the ferry was carrying enough lifeboats al-ahram a leading cairo newspaper said in an unattributed report today that the vessel left the charted navigation channel to take a shortcut it said naval authorities warned the skipper back on course to avoid the area's abundant coral reefs but strong winds sent the boat out of control the newspaper said the boat's first mate mahmoud soleiman rizake said a terrible explosion from the collision awoke him in his cabin water flooded the ship in 10 minutes causing it to sink he said adding that he jumped overboard and swam until a rescue boat picked him up the temperature of the water was not immediately known but the air temperature was about 50 degrees and many of the survivors were treated for exposure at least 118 of the survivors were hospitalized el-gazzar the deputy port security chief said all but 10 of the passengers were egyptians associated press usa safaga egypt street sj san jose mercury news 911216 monday december 1a 1991 west photo map ca 626 monday december 16 1991 00351097sj1 copyright 1991 san jose mercury news 1 eng front sjmn91-06351209 06351209 photo map photo associated press an egyptian pulled from sunken ferry sunday in stormy red sea makes his way to a rescue vehicle color map associated press red sea showing the port of origin and the port where the barge sank color boat disaster multiple death egypt missing person hunt the engineer of a ferry that sank off this red sea port leaving more than 400 people missing today denied accusations of widespread negligence on the part of the ship's crew mahmoud moharram engineer of the salem express ackn